<% content_for :title, "About Pod Tracker" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Pod Tracker is a self-hosted, open-source, bracket-aware Commander companion. Card facts come from Scryfall. Commander rules come from mtgcommander.net. AI is allowed to interpret, never to invent." %>

<article class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
  <header class="space-y-3">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-emerald-300">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white sm:text-4xl">About Pod Tracker</h1>
  </header>

  <p>Pod Tracker is a Commander companion built to make Rule 0 conversations easier and pod analysis honest. It reads decklists, places them on the official Commander Brackets system, surfaces the cards and patterns that drove the placement, and produces a pregame brief you can paste into chat.</p>

  <p>The project is self-hosted, open-source, and run by one person — <a href="https://github.com/dunamismax" class="underline hover:text-zinc-300">dunamismax</a>. Card facts come from <a class="underline hover:text-zinc-300" href="https://scryfall.com">Scryfall</a> bulk data. Commander rules and the banned list come from <a class="underline hover:text-zinc-300" href="https://mtgcommander.net">mtgcommander.net</a>. The Commander Brackets list is sourced from Wizards of the Coast's published bracket data and refreshed as Wizards updates it. AI evaluation is allowed to interpret deterministic facts; it is never the rules authority.</p>

  <p>The name "Pod Tracker" reflects the goal: less guessing, more shared language, more games where everyone gets to play.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">What you can do without an account</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
    <li>Read the <%= link_to "full bracket guide", brackets_path, class: "underline hover:text-zinc-300" %>.</li>
    <li>Browse the <%= link_to "Game Changers list", game_changers_path, class: "underline hover:text-zinc-300" %>.</li>
    <li>Copy the <%= link_to "pregame template", pregame_template_path, class: "underline hover:text-zinc-300" %>.</li>
    <li>Open shared pod links other users send you.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">What needs an account</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
    <li>Importing decks (paste, file, public Archidekt URL, public Moxfield URL).</li>
    <li>Running deterministic deck and pod analysis.</li>
    <li>Building pods of 2–4 of your own decks and generating Rule 0 briefs.</li>
    <li>Tracking game-night sessions and matchup notes (in progress).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Fan content notice</h2>
  <p>Pod Tracker is unofficial fan content. It is not approved, endorsed, or sponsored by Wizards of the Coast. Portions of Magic: The Gathering materials are property of Wizards of the Coast LLC. Use of card names, card text, images, and related material follows Wizards' Fan Content Policy and source-specific data terms.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Source</h2>
  <p><a href="https://github.com/dunamismax/pod-tracker" class="underline hover:text-zinc-300">github.com/dunamismax/pod-tracker</a> — GPLv3-licensed.</p>
</article>
